{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Log entries with the same trace ID are grouped together regardless of which microservice emitted them.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Grouping correctness sits at the boundary between parsing/ingestion and correlation modules. A pure unit test of a grouping helper can miss real failures from schema mapping differences across service log formats.","test_description":"Feed mixed JSON log lines from at least 3 simulated services into the real ingestion + normalization + correlation pipeline (local files/streams). Assert that all records sharing a trace ID end up in one correlated request group, independent of service name/source.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The timeline view orders entries by timestamp, correctly handling clock skew of up to 500ms between services.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Clock-skew handling is usually implemented across ordering logic plus normalization/timeline assembly. Unit tests of sort logic alone can miss failures in how timestamps are parsed, normalized, and merged across service streams.","test_description":"Run the real timeline builder on correlated logs from multiple services with controlled skew in the [-500ms, +500ms] range, including near-boundary cases (e.g., 499ms/500ms). Verify final timeline order matches expected causal order under the skew rule.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A latency spike (p99 above 3x the baseline) is detected and flagged in the anomaly report.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure boundary is between metric aggregation (baseline + p99 computation) and anomaly reporting. Mocking one side can hide wiring mistakes (wrong window, wrong metric field, threshold application mismatch) even if the math function itself is correct.","test_description":"Ingest deterministic synthetic logs with a known baseline period and a spike period where p99 is >3x baseline. Execute the real aggregation + anomaly report modules together and assert the spike is flagged with the expected metric context.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.4,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Malformed JSON log entries are skipped without crashing the pipeline, and the count of skipped entries is reported.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This requires real parser error propagation through the ingest pipeline and reporting counters. A mocked parser or isolated function test can miss crash paths and counter/report wiring failures.","test_description":"Provide an input batch mixing valid JSON logs and malformed lines to the real ingest pipeline. Assert: process completes, valid entries are still processed, malformed lines are skipped, and skipped-count in output/report equals the exact malformed count.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The tool handles a burst of 10,000 log entries per second without dropping entries or falling behind.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Throughput/backpressure/drop behavior depends on runtime scheduling, queues, I/O, and process-level performance characteristics. In-process mocks can hide real bottlenecks and timing failures.","test_description":"Run a load test against the built service/process with a real log generator producing 10k entries/sec for a sustained interval. Measure ingest rate, end-to-end lag, and total in vs out counts; fail on any dropped entries or lag growth beyond defined SLO.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.8,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}}]}
